<h2>Select Handler Demo</h2>

The <b><a name="sel_demo">select handler demo</a></b> shows how to use the following select handler attributes: ...
<p>
xxx, zzz, : <select sep=", "><from>xxx <em>xx yy zz</em> zzz</from> #text</select>
<p>
xxx, zzz, : <select sep=", "><from><b>what the heck</b> <em>xx yy zz</em> zzz</from><child>2</child></select>

<p>

<hr>
<a name="sel_text"><h3> Select a Text Node </h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Returns all text nodes from the parse tree.  In the following example, there 
is a single text node.  This example returns this node:  Single text node.
<p>
<b> Input:      </b>&lt;select&gt;&lt;from&gt;Single text node&lt;/from&gt; #text &lt;/select&gt;
<p>
<b> Result:     </b><select><from>Single text node</from> #text </select>
<hr>

<a name="sel_septext"><h3> Select a Split Text Node </h3></a>
<b> Description:</b> Returns all text nodes from the parse tree.  In the following example, a 
separator has been added to separate the nodes when printed out.  This example
returns the two text nodes: text1 and text2.  It does not return the text from the marked up
node bold1.
three nodes:  Single text node.
<p>
<b> Input: </b>&lt;select sep=", "&gt;&lt;from&gt;text1 &lt;em&gt;bold1&lt;/em&gt; text2 &lt;/from&gt; #text &lt;/select&gt;
<p>
<b> Result:     </b><select sep=", "><from>text1 <em>bold1</em> text2 </from> #text </select>

<hr>

TEST EXAMPLE: <br>
<b> Result: </b><select sep=", "><from>text1<em>bold1</em>text2</from><child>em</child></select>
